OL,6,FTuesday was an Opposition Day at
OL,7,FStormont, with the SDLP controlling
OL,8,Fthe order of business in the Assembly
OL,9,Fchamber.
OL,11,FThe party's first motion of the day
OL,12,Ffocused on the UK Government's
OL,13,Fcontentious two-child-limit welfare
OL,14,Fpolicy, which restricts families to
OL,15,Fclaiming Universal Credit or Child Tax
OL,16,FCredit support for only their first
OL,17,Ftwo children, with no further support
OL,18,Fpaid out for a third child or
OL,19,Fsubsequent children.
