OL,6,FOn the substance of the debate, Mr
OL,7,FLyons made clear he was opposed to the
OL,8,Ftwo-child limit. But he cited the cost
OL,9,Fimplications of removing it in
OL,10,FNorthern Ireland while it remained in
OL,11,Fplace elsewhere in the UK.
OL,13,FHe said it would cost Stormont more
OL,14,Fthan #56 million a year ` a total that
OL,15,Fexcluded the associated IT and
OL,16,Fadministrative costs of setting up a
OL,17,Fdifferent system.
